✔️ Recommended Setup (Production Style)

Best setup:

PostgreSQL runs automatically

Django connects automatically

No manual commands

Perfect — this Recommended Production Setup is exactly what you want. It ensures your Django site works reliably without manual steps. Here’s how to configure it properly on Windows so PostgreSQL runs automatically and Django connects automatically.

✅ Step 1 — Make PostgreSQL Start Automatically
1️⃣ Open Windows Services

Press:

Windows + R

Type:

services.msc

Press Enter

2️⃣ Find PostgreSQL Service

Look for something like:

postgresql-x64-18

or

PostgreSQL Server 18
3️⃣ Set Startup to Automatic

Right-click → Properties

Set:

Startup Type = Automatic

Click:

Apply → OK
4️⃣ Start the Service

Right-click:

Start

✅ Now PostgreSQL will always start when Windows starts.

No need for:

pg_ctl start

ever again.

✅ Step 2 — Confirm PostgreSQL Runs Automatically

Restart your computer.

Then test:

netstat -ano | findstr 2456

You should see:

LISTENING

✅ Means PostgreSQL auto-start works.

✅ Step 3 — Make Django Connect Automatically

Make sure settings.py is correct:

DATABASES = {
    'default': {
        'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.postgresql',
        'NAME': 'yourdbname',
        'USER': 'postgres',
        'PASSWORD': 'yourpassword',
        'HOST': 'localhost',
        'PORT': 'your port umber',
    }
}

No changes needed after this.

Django connects automatically.

✅ Step 4 — Test Automatic Setup

Run:

python manage.py runserver

Open:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin

If it loads:

✅ Database auto-connect works.

